{"questionId":"25981","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A scientist conducted a nine-week experiment on two plants, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>, of the same species.&nbsp;He wanted to determine the effect of using a new plant fertilizer. Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> was given fertilizer&nbsp;regularly, while Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> was not.</p>\n<p>The scientist found that the height of Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> weeks can be modelled by the&nbsp;function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>27</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The scientist found that the height of Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> weeks can be modelled by the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>32</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0074</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7034</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>88332</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>88</mn></math>&nbsp;(weeks)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25981","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ2.10b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the values of t when hAt=hBt.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.8—Solving trig equations","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}